1. Difference between wget and curl command
Note: execute wget and curl with an example
- wget command is to be used mainly to download the files from the internet
- curl command is used to transfer data between the client and the server and also to test API
Example for the wget command-
Below I downloaded the file named “robots.txt” from “www.google.com” , so I used 
Syntax: wget https://www.google.com/robots.txt
 






Example for curl command-
Below I used the curl command to display the contents of the file named “robots.txt” from “www.google.com” into the terminal,
Syntax: curl https://www.google.com/robots.txt
 


